title: House of Secrets # 1-25 (Vertigo)
description:
25 issues published by Vertigo 1996-1999

House of Secrets was an occult and horror-themed comic book series written by Steven T. Seagle. The art was by Teddy Kristiansen, with occasional assistance by Christian HÃƒÂ¸jgaard, Guy Davis, Duncan Fegredo and the Pander Brothers. It debuted in October 1996, published by the Vertigo imprint of DC Comics, and ran for 25 issues, followed by a two-issue limited series House of Secrets: Facade, by the same creative team in 2001.
Although its title was based on the classic House of Secrets series that ran from 1956 to 1976, it was an otherwise unrelated series.
